title: Junior Software Engineer
content:
ABOUT EXODUSPOINT
ExodusPoint Capital, founded in 2017 by Michael Gelband and Hyung Lee, began managing investor capital in 2018. The firm employs a global multi-strategy investment approach, seeking to deliver compelling asymmetric returns by combining complementary liquid strategies managed by experienced investment professionals within a robust risk framework. With a global headcount of over 600 employees and AUM of $13.5B, ExodusPoint brings together an accomplished team with hands-on experience running multi-manager businesses to create an institutional investment management firm. 
OVERVIEW OF THE JOB DESCRIPTION 
We are looking for motivated technologists who want to directly contribute to our business. Candidates should have an interest in financial services, strong object-oriented programming knowledge in Python, and solid critical thinking ability. Our teams work collaboratively, so we are looking for candidates who can demonstrate excellent teamwork and communication abilities.
Responsibilities:
Automation, Data ETL, and customized reporting
Sustainably Engineer: develop, and support solutions that are highly available, scalable, and resilient that are monitored from end to end
Work with a broad set of third-party services and develop integrations that will enable efficiencies for the business across platforms
Work with key stakeholders to understand business requirements and develop solutions to meet those needs with the end user experience as a focus
Qualifications:
Bachelorâ€™s degree or working toward a Masterâ€™s degree in Computer Science or related field
On track for a minimum 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent)
Strong Object-Oriented Programming skills in Python
Demonstrate capacity for innovative thinking and strong problem solving
Demonstrate effective communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to interact with a variety of people
Demonstrate integrity and ethics by earning otherâ€™s trust and respect through consistent honesty and professionalism in all interactions
Display clear motivation for exploring a Technology career within financial services
Display evidence of strong teamwork, leadership and the ability to work in a fast-paced environment
Fluency in written and spoken English is a pre-requisite
Show demonstrable evidence of self-learning outside of studies, and efforts to advance technical skills
Knowledge and Experience in Agile Methodology (is a plus)
Knowledge and Experience in Data Engineering and Analytics (is a plus)
Knowledge and Experience in Machine Learning & Natural Language Processing (is a plus)
